1
00:01:29,350 --> 00:01:34,930
[Our Dazzling Days]

2
00:01:35,360 --> 00:01:37,780
[Episode 16]

3
00:02:29,190 --> 00:02:30,590
Follow the numbers.

4
00:02:49,070 --> 00:02:51,190
What the hell is that thing you welded?

5
00:02:51,190 --> 00:02:52,560
You call that a proper job?
What is it supposed to be?

6
00:02:52,560 --> 00:02:54,120
Mentor, an ordinary man
wouldn't be able to tell.

7
00:02:54,120 --> 00:02:55,000
It's solid as hell.

8
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:57,000
How come an ordinary man can't tell?

9
00:02:58,550 --> 00:02:59,680
Let me tell you, Shi.

10
00:02:59,910 --> 00:03:00,960
We're industrial workers,

11
00:03:00,960 --> 00:03:01,750
got that?

12
00:03:02,020 --> 00:03:03,240
Whether you're building airplanes,

13
00:03:03,240 --> 00:03:03,960
cannons,

14
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:05,360
or even just a tiny part,

15
00:03:05,710 --> 00:03:07,800
anything that comes out of your hands

16
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:08,750
represents me—
Ding Guoqiang's apprentice,

17
00:03:08,750 --> 00:03:09,680
got it?

18
00:03:11,530 --> 00:03:12,360
If you're not ashamed,

19
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:13,150
I am.

20
00:03:14,630 --> 00:03:16,030
What kind of weld is this?

21
00:03:16,070 --> 00:03:18,270
It looks like an old lady's fungal nail.

22
00:03:19,170 --> 00:03:20,829
It's all rough. Weld it again.

23
00:03:22,360 --> 00:03:24,490
What's spinning in that head of yours?

24
00:03:24,680 --> 00:03:25,630
I heard you.

25
00:03:29,990 --> 00:03:30,780
Be careful.

26
00:03:30,940 --> 00:03:31,410
Okay.

27
00:03:33,750 --> 00:03:35,079
Put some effort into it.

28
00:03:35,310 --> 00:03:36,540
Two more boxes to go.

29
00:03:37,829 --> 00:03:38,550
Okay.

30
00:03:38,750 --> 00:03:39,750
It's almost done.

31
00:03:39,980 --> 00:03:42,140
Uncle, sorry to take up your time.

32
00:03:42,170 --> 00:03:43,360
When I get the payment,

33
00:03:43,360 --> 00:03:45,000
I'll pay you back immediately.

34
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:46,260
It's no trouble at all.

35
00:03:46,520 --> 00:03:47,560
I drive a taxi now,

36
00:03:47,560 --> 00:03:48,960
so I make my own schedule.

37
00:03:49,120 --> 00:03:50,560
It doesn't matter if it's early or late.

38
00:03:50,560 --> 00:03:51,960
I still have to thank you.

39
00:03:52,160 --> 00:03:54,280
Seeing you create work for yourself

40
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:56,240
makes me really happy.

41
00:03:56,240 --> 00:03:57,710
Xia Lei's the real deal.

42
00:03:57,710 --> 00:03:59,960
If it weren't for him

43
00:03:59,960 --> 00:04:01,430
setting up that website to find jobs,

44
00:04:01,430 --> 00:04:03,120
there's no way
I could've reached this client.

45
00:04:03,120 --> 00:04:04,210
We all rely on Xia Lei.

46
00:04:04,210 --> 00:04:06,340
When you first said he built that site,

47
00:04:06,520 --> 00:04:08,080
I was honestly nervous—

48
00:04:08,080 --> 00:04:09,700
had no clue what he was messing with.

49
00:04:09,700 --> 00:04:11,020
Now I understand a bit more,

50
00:04:11,020 --> 00:04:11,770
and I'm much more relieved.

51
00:04:11,770 --> 00:04:13,120
He's really good.

52
00:04:13,120 --> 00:04:14,150
He's not messing around.

53
00:04:14,150 --> 00:04:16,750
You and Xia Lei are fighting side by side

54
00:04:16,769 --> 00:04:18,230
like when you were little.

55
00:04:18,269 --> 00:04:18,920
I'm so happy.

56
00:04:18,920 --> 00:04:21,070
We're be standing together
our whole lives, right?

57
00:04:21,070 --> 00:04:22,040
We've grown up together
since we were kids.

58
00:04:22,040 --> 00:04:23,000
Our bond is different.

59
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:23,310
Yes.

60
00:04:23,310 --> 00:04:24,040
Don't worry, Uncle.

61
00:04:24,040 --> 00:04:25,900
Have you told Xiaodan about this?

62
00:04:26,750 --> 00:04:29,640
Not yet. The contract isn't signed,

63
00:04:29,750 --> 00:04:31,350
so I'll wait till everything's finalized

64
00:04:31,350 --> 00:04:32,460
before telling her.

65
00:04:32,460 --> 00:04:35,200
Yeah, a man's gotta be dependable
in front of his woman.

66
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:36,830
I've been dependable my whole life.

67
00:04:36,830 --> 00:04:37,800
-Xiaoman!
-I believe that.

68
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:39,290
Mr. Xia, it's all installed.

69
00:04:39,290 --> 00:04:39,820
Okay.

70
00:04:39,880 --> 00:04:40,610
-Yes.
-Okay.

71
00:04:40,750 --> 00:04:41,510
Do these things

72
00:04:41,510 --> 00:04:42,750
just need to go to
the railway freight yard?

73
00:04:42,750 --> 00:04:44,470
Yes, they'll be taken by train later.

74
00:04:44,470 --> 00:04:45,360
-We've contacted them.
-Let's go.

75
00:04:45,360 --> 00:04:46,310
Let's go.

76
00:04:48,360 --> 00:04:49,190
Slow down.

77
00:04:55,080 --> 00:04:55,640
Mentor,

78
00:04:56,430 --> 00:04:58,159
what's for dinner tonight?

79
00:04:58,650 --> 00:05:00,390
Do you have a grudge against my wife?

80
00:05:00,390 --> 00:05:02,120
Can't you let her rest for a day?

81
00:05:02,430 --> 00:05:03,600
I didn't mean that. If she doesn't cook,

82
00:05:03,600 --> 00:05:04,830
I'll go over and cook.

83
00:05:04,830 --> 00:05:05,960
That's what I meant.

84
00:05:06,240 --> 00:05:06,970
He's scared.

85
00:05:08,030 --> 00:05:09,160
Look who's back.

86
00:05:09,270 --> 00:05:10,400
Isn't that Xiaoman?

87
00:05:11,960 --> 00:05:13,430
Why are his hands empty?

88
00:05:13,430 --> 00:05:14,430
Watch your mouth.

89
00:05:14,430 --> 00:05:15,830
You're such a jinx.

90
00:05:16,130 --> 00:05:17,990
Come on, let's see what happened.

91
00:05:18,330 --> 00:05:18,810
No way.

92
00:05:18,840 --> 00:05:19,770
I ran all the way.

93
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:20,830
Mentor,

94
00:05:21,430 --> 00:05:24,270
the factory got back to us.

95
00:05:24,830 --> 00:05:27,630
They said our products are good

96
00:05:28,390 --> 00:05:29,240
and

97
00:05:30,310 --> 00:05:32,240
they're willing to place an order.

98
00:05:32,690 --> 00:05:33,659
Right after,

99
00:05:33,690 --> 00:05:36,090
he transferred the initial payment to us.

100
00:05:38,130 --> 00:05:39,100
Don't tear it.

101
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:40,159
Easy.

102
00:05:40,430 --> 00:05:41,070
Let me see.

103
00:05:41,070 --> 00:05:41,870
Don't tear it.

104
00:05:42,310 --> 00:05:42,750
Okay.

105
00:05:43,120 --> 00:05:43,830
Okay.

106
00:05:44,159 --> 00:05:44,510
For real?

107
00:05:44,510 --> 00:05:46,170
Hurry up. Mentor is speaking.

108
00:05:46,330 --> 00:05:47,390
Pack it up. Don't lose it.

109
00:05:47,390 --> 00:05:48,120
Give it to me.

110
00:05:48,120 --> 00:05:49,180
What are you doing?

111
00:05:49,320 --> 00:05:50,380
Show some manners.

112
00:05:50,630 --> 00:05:51,690
Put it away safely.

113
00:05:52,159 --> 00:05:53,800
That workshop director's so stingy—

114
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:54,920
for Xiaoman to get the money back,

115
00:05:54,920 --> 00:05:56,650
he must've talked his head off.

116
00:05:57,110 --> 00:05:58,380
-Xiaoman.
-Not bad.

117
00:05:59,159 --> 00:06:01,920
Xiaoman, are they really willing
to pay the deposit?

118
00:06:01,920 --> 00:06:02,750
What deposit?

119
00:06:02,750 --> 00:06:03,510
They aren't stupid.

120
00:06:03,510 --> 00:06:05,430
Who pays without seeing the goods?

121
00:06:05,430 --> 00:06:07,390
But then I told the Director,

122
00:06:07,830 --> 00:06:08,480
I said,

123
00:06:08,480 --> 00:06:10,330
"If you don't sign the contract with them,

124
00:06:10,330 --> 00:06:11,260
and don't agree,

125
00:06:11,630 --> 00:06:13,240
they'll skip me

126
00:06:13,240 --> 00:06:15,060
and sign with
the Plant Director directly."

127
00:06:15,060 --> 00:06:16,120
So the Director gave in.

128
00:06:16,120 --> 00:06:18,310
He said once their purchaser arrives,

129
00:06:18,630 --> 00:06:20,190
he'll sign the contract immediately.

130
00:06:20,190 --> 00:06:20,870
It's done.

131
00:06:21,240 --> 00:06:21,920
Mentor,

132
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:22,830
it's a great occasion.

133
00:06:22,830 --> 00:06:24,490
We have to drink to celebrate.

134
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:26,390
We really have to drink.

135
00:06:26,390 --> 00:06:27,320
Yeah, we should.

136
00:06:27,430 --> 00:06:28,800
We have to work tonight.

137
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:30,360
Don't you have any sense of priority?
Get back to work.

138
00:06:30,360 --> 00:06:31,040
Mentor, I...

139
00:06:31,040 --> 00:06:31,830
I've basically worked a whole year's worth

140
00:06:31,830 --> 00:06:34,040
of shifts these past days.

141
00:06:34,040 --> 00:06:35,300
Can't we have a day off?

142
00:06:40,750 --> 00:06:41,950
Silly, are you still welding?

143
00:06:41,950 --> 00:06:42,600
Lulu!

144
00:06:43,770 --> 00:06:44,740
Why are you here?

145
00:06:44,760 --> 00:06:45,720
To see you.

146
00:07:14,750 --> 00:07:15,810
-Dongdong!
-Lulu!

147
00:07:16,070 --> 00:07:17,630
Hurry, Dongdong. Run!

148
00:07:17,750 --> 00:07:18,800
Let's go.

149
00:07:19,530 --> 00:07:20,170
Hurry up!

150
00:07:25,270 --> 00:07:26,040
Hurry.

151
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:30,390
Go.

152
00:07:37,560 --> 00:07:38,390
Run!

153
00:07:40,120 --> 00:07:40,920
What's wrong?

154
00:07:42,909 --> 00:07:43,770
What happened?

155
00:07:47,190 --> 00:07:48,450
Where is Shi Dongming?

156
00:07:49,240 --> 00:07:50,480
You're screwed.

157
00:07:50,630 --> 00:07:51,360
He's inside.

158
00:07:51,360 --> 00:07:53,360
Shi!

159
00:07:53,360 --> 00:07:54,159
Don't go in.

160
00:07:54,390 --> 00:07:55,190
Give me the light.

161
00:07:55,190 --> 00:07:55,830
Dongming!

162
00:07:55,830 --> 00:07:56,760
It's dangerous.

163
00:07:56,870 --> 00:07:57,680
Dongming!

164
00:07:58,070 --> 00:07:59,070
Shi!

165
00:08:00,040 --> 00:08:01,040
Shi Dongming!

166
00:08:01,680 --> 00:08:02,480
Xiaoman!

167
00:08:03,270 --> 00:08:04,400
Xiaoman! Come back!

168
00:08:14,190 --> 00:08:14,990
Xiaoman!

169
00:08:15,830 --> 00:08:17,190
Xiaoman, come back!

170
00:08:17,190 --> 00:08:18,510
Mentor, I'm here.

171
00:08:19,120 --> 00:08:19,830
Xiaoman!

172
00:08:20,070 --> 00:08:21,000
Mentor!

173
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:22,540
Come back!

174
00:08:30,160 --> 00:08:31,950
Xiaoman.

175
00:08:31,950 --> 00:08:33,350
Stop working. Come here.

176
00:08:33,510 --> 00:08:34,000
What's wrong?

177
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:35,000
Hurry up.

178
00:08:36,480 --> 00:08:38,320
What is it?

179
00:08:38,320 --> 00:08:39,520
Something happened.

180
00:08:40,840 --> 00:08:41,700
What happened?

181
00:08:42,080 --> 00:08:44,390
The factory leadership held a meeting —
they're going to discipline you guys.

182
00:08:44,390 --> 00:08:45,250
Discipline us?

183
00:08:46,030 --> 00:08:47,240
What kind of punishment?

184
00:08:47,240 --> 00:08:48,570
It won't be light, anyway.

185
00:08:48,570 --> 00:08:49,090
Let me tell you,

186
00:08:49,090 --> 00:08:50,240
the workshop director is denying

187
00:08:50,240 --> 00:08:52,330
he ever approved you
to produce those gas stove brackets.

188
00:08:52,330 --> 00:08:53,450
Now the factory's

189
00:08:53,470 --> 00:08:55,120
charging you with misusing state assets

190
00:08:55,120 --> 00:08:57,270
for private work,

191
00:08:57,440 --> 00:08:58,670
violating safety regulations,

192
00:08:58,670 --> 00:09:00,510
and causing a major accident
and financial losses—

193
00:09:00,510 --> 00:09:01,370
all that stuff.

194
00:09:01,600 --> 00:09:03,000
Anyway, you've all been named.

195
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:03,840
What are you talking about?

196
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:05,240
He clearly promised me personally.

197
00:09:05,240 --> 00:09:06,720
He said he agreed in principle.

198
00:09:06,720 --> 00:09:08,240
We only started after he said yes.

199
00:09:08,240 --> 00:09:09,910
Agreed in principle?

200
00:09:09,910 --> 00:09:11,960
That just means if things go well,
it's because of him—

201
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:12,910
but if something goes wrong,

202
00:09:12,910 --> 00:09:14,510
it has nothing to do with him.

203
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:19,250
Okay, okay. I know.

204
00:09:19,250 --> 00:09:20,710
Wait, where are you going?

205
00:09:20,710 --> 00:09:22,310
Xiaoman, listen to me!

206
00:09:22,580 --> 00:09:23,520
Wait a second.

207
00:09:26,360 --> 00:09:27,160
What's wrong?

208
00:09:27,390 --> 00:09:28,590
Something happened.

209
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:32,270
Wait a second. Let me tell you!

210
00:09:36,910 --> 00:09:37,840
Plant Director.

211
00:09:38,120 --> 00:09:39,050
Plant Director.

212
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:40,000
Plant Director, this...

213
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:41,440
We were indeed wrong about this.

214
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:43,080
But it has nothing to do with the others.

215
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:44,510
Mr. Ding and the others didn't know.

216
00:09:44,510 --> 00:09:46,120
I told them the Director agreed,

217
00:09:46,120 --> 00:09:47,390
and then we started working.

218
00:09:47,390 --> 00:09:48,600
It really has nothing to do with them.

219
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:49,240
So, about this...

220
00:09:49,240 --> 00:09:50,360
You can't punish everyone.

221
00:09:50,360 --> 00:09:51,390
If you have to punish someone, punish me.

222
00:09:51,390 --> 00:09:52,520
You can even fire me.

223
00:09:52,750 --> 00:09:54,270
Is this just about getting fired?

224
00:09:54,270 --> 00:09:56,330
You could be held criminally liable.

225
00:09:56,840 --> 00:09:58,040
Okay, Plant Director.

226
00:09:58,040 --> 00:09:59,140
Plant Director, no problem.

227
00:09:59,140 --> 00:10:00,000
If you want to punish me,

228
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:00,750
any punishment is fine.

229
00:10:00,750 --> 00:10:04,010
But it really has nothing to do
with Mr. Ding and the others.

230
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:05,730
What is wrong with you guys?

231
00:10:06,280 --> 00:10:07,810
Do you have any discipline?

232
00:10:08,080 --> 00:10:09,540
We are a military factory!

233
00:10:11,480 --> 00:10:12,240
Meng.

234
00:10:13,410 --> 00:10:14,290
Director Meng.

235
00:10:16,420 --> 00:10:18,730
Everyone's seen the changes in the factory

236
00:10:18,730 --> 00:10:19,930
these past two years.

237
00:10:21,910 --> 00:10:22,670
The reason we

238
00:10:22,670 --> 00:10:24,480
took the risk to do this job

239
00:10:24,480 --> 00:10:25,630
was simply to help everyone

240
00:10:25,630 --> 00:10:27,040
get an extra month's bonus.

241
00:10:27,040 --> 00:10:27,870
It's that simple.

242
00:10:27,870 --> 00:10:30,200
If you're talking about selfish motives—

243
00:10:30,810 --> 00:10:31,740
there were none.

244
00:10:32,390 --> 00:10:34,190
If it was for the factory's good,

245
00:10:34,440 --> 00:10:37,240
then why sneak around
and do private work at night?

246
00:10:40,020 --> 00:10:42,390
Do you really think Xiaoman would've dared

247
00:10:42,390 --> 00:10:44,850
without the workshop director's approval?

248
00:10:46,840 --> 00:10:50,320
Using scrap materials
to make gas stove brackets—

249
00:10:50,320 --> 00:10:51,820
that was approved by him too.

250
00:10:51,820 --> 00:10:52,300
Wait.

251
00:10:52,790 --> 00:10:54,120
Even working at night

252
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:57,320
was approved
by the director in principle.

253
00:10:57,770 --> 00:10:59,460
Not me! I never did!

254
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:00,910
I ought to slap you!

255
00:11:01,270 --> 00:11:03,320
Hey, Ding, even if you slap me,

256
00:11:03,320 --> 00:11:04,080
that won't do.

257
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:05,000
There is no evidence.

258
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:06,870
Show me the evidence.

259
00:11:08,990 --> 00:11:09,670
I don't have any.

260
00:11:09,670 --> 00:11:10,600
What evidence do you want?

261
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:11,240
You want evidence?

262
00:11:11,240 --> 00:11:13,150
This is serious business.

263
00:11:15,320 --> 00:11:16,600
Director of Workshop 1,

264
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:17,750
did you ever say

265
00:11:17,750 --> 00:11:19,150
you agreed in principle?

266
00:11:19,310 --> 00:11:22,220
Plant Director,
I certainly didn't say that.

267
00:11:22,510 --> 00:11:24,000
No, he did say it.

268
00:11:25,720 --> 00:11:27,150
But then again,

269
00:11:27,640 --> 00:11:29,910
did I not explain clearly?

270
00:11:30,220 --> 00:11:32,740
Xiaoman, did you misunderstand?

271
00:11:33,080 --> 00:11:34,600
Right, Plant Director.

272
00:11:34,750 --> 00:11:36,790
I messed this up.

273
00:11:36,790 --> 00:11:37,910
I passed on the wrong message.

274
00:11:37,910 --> 00:11:39,390
It has nothing to do with anyone else.

275
00:11:39,390 --> 00:11:40,190
Stop talking.

276
00:11:49,790 --> 00:11:51,650
Zhao Hai, Director of Workshop 1,

277
00:11:51,870 --> 00:11:53,800
you are singled out for criticism!

278
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:54,860
Ding Guoqiang,

279
00:11:55,150 --> 00:11:56,010
Zhang Xiaoman,

280
00:11:56,360 --> 00:11:57,160
Shi Dongming,

281
00:11:57,200 --> 00:11:57,790
Wang Dongdong,

282
00:11:57,790 --> 00:12:00,080
and all workers who took on private jobs

283
00:12:01,150 --> 00:12:02,550
are suspended from duty.

284
00:12:11,550 --> 00:12:12,150
Open up.

285
00:12:16,090 --> 00:12:18,240
Mr. Ding,
just clocked in and already clocking out?

286
00:12:18,240 --> 00:12:19,500
Just a shift rotation.

287
00:12:19,870 --> 00:12:20,810
Just switching shifts.

288
00:12:20,810 --> 00:12:24,130
[East Integrated Chemical Plant]

289
00:12:27,030 --> 00:12:27,960
I'll make a call.

290
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:38,560
Hello.

291
00:12:39,440 --> 00:12:40,080
Xia Lei.

292
00:12:40,730 --> 00:12:41,330
Xiaoman.

293
00:12:41,510 --> 00:12:42,240
Well,

294
00:12:44,070 --> 00:12:47,760
I might not be able to deliver the goods.

295
00:12:48,520 --> 00:12:49,850
The workshop exploded.

296
00:12:53,120 --> 00:12:54,840
Are you okay?

297
00:12:55,510 --> 00:12:56,320
I'm fine.

298
00:12:57,480 --> 00:12:57,970
I...

299
00:12:58,000 --> 00:12:59,080
No one was hurt.

300
00:13:00,200 --> 00:13:02,930
It's a blessing in disguise
that everyone is safe.

301
00:13:02,930 --> 00:13:04,800
Don't worry about anything else.

302
00:13:05,600 --> 00:13:06,670
I'm sorry.

303
00:13:08,750 --> 00:13:09,510
Take care.

304
00:13:11,320 --> 00:13:12,520
Okay. I'm hanging up.

305
00:13:12,750 --> 00:13:13,480
Okay. Bye.

306
00:13:38,320 --> 00:13:38,910
Lei.

307
00:13:41,670 --> 00:13:42,530
What happened?

308
00:13:44,930 --> 00:13:45,660
It exploded.

309
00:13:46,270 --> 00:13:47,130
What exploded?

310
00:13:49,130 --> 00:13:52,130
The workshop producing
gas stove brackets exploded.

311
00:14:03,200 --> 00:14:05,170
Good thing we didn't sign an
agency agreement for this deal.

312
00:14:05,170 --> 00:14:06,170
We can handle it.

313
00:14:06,580 --> 00:14:07,190
No rush.

314
00:14:07,290 --> 00:14:08,270
We won't lose much.

315
00:14:08,270 --> 00:14:10,320
But we work in the internet industry.

316
00:14:10,320 --> 00:14:12,720
Information spreads incredibly fast now.

317
00:14:13,550 --> 00:14:14,480
What do you mean?

318
00:14:14,630 --> 00:14:16,270
Our recent clients

319
00:14:16,270 --> 00:14:17,390
only came after hearing

320
00:14:17,390 --> 00:14:19,670
we signed this deal.

321
00:14:19,980 --> 00:14:21,030
Now that they

322
00:14:23,080 --> 00:14:24,240
know about this...

323
00:14:30,210 --> 00:14:31,020
Hello, Mr. Li.

324
00:14:32,150 --> 00:14:33,790
It's Fan.

325
00:14:34,360 --> 00:14:35,200
Yes.

326
00:14:36,440 --> 00:14:37,700
Are you busy right now?

327
00:14:38,360 --> 00:14:39,620
I just wanted to check—

328
00:14:39,840 --> 00:14:42,110
our order is still going ahead
as planned, right?

329
00:14:42,110 --> 00:14:44,040
There aren't any problems, right?

330
00:14:44,510 --> 00:14:45,470
That's good.

331
00:14:45,600 --> 00:14:46,240
Okay.

332
00:14:46,480 --> 00:14:47,480
Do you have time tonight?

333
00:14:47,480 --> 00:14:48,750
Let's get together.

334
00:14:48,900 --> 00:14:51,410
Am I not cut out for starting a business?

335
00:14:52,790 --> 00:14:54,030
Let's go to karaoke.

336
00:14:54,030 --> 00:14:55,550
It's okay.

337
00:14:57,510 --> 00:14:58,970
Just come out and hang out.

338
00:15:03,910 --> 00:15:06,870
In this dump, the more you do,
the more you screw up.

339
00:15:07,590 --> 00:15:10,250
If I wasn't trying to make money
for the factory,

340
00:15:10,270 --> 00:15:12,200
I wouldn't be stuck on suspension.

341
00:15:12,510 --> 00:15:14,030
Why do you talk so much?

342
00:15:14,030 --> 00:15:15,670
Xiaoman almost got blown to death
and didn't complain.

343
00:15:15,670 --> 00:15:16,960
What are you yapping about?

344
00:15:16,960 --> 00:15:19,030
Mr. Ding, I almost got blown up too.

345
00:15:19,440 --> 00:15:20,630
Well... We're both your apprentices.

346
00:15:20,630 --> 00:15:21,550
Why don't you care about me?

347
00:15:21,550 --> 00:15:22,360
Why not? You...

348
00:15:22,360 --> 00:15:23,480
You're getting more and more unruly.

349
00:15:23,480 --> 00:15:25,000
Who do you think you're talking to?

350
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:26,000
Are you drinking?

351
00:15:26,790 --> 00:15:28,250
I'll shut up. I'll shut up.

352
00:15:28,470 --> 00:15:29,800
Why are you getting mad?

353
00:15:30,100 --> 00:15:30,800
I just started.

354
00:15:30,800 --> 00:15:32,200
I haven't really had any.

355
00:15:33,780 --> 00:15:34,910
Put that thing down.

356
00:15:36,310 --> 00:15:36,970
Put it down!

357
00:15:38,440 --> 00:15:39,550
You're still drinking?

358
00:15:39,550 --> 00:15:41,870
Don't you know how the accident happened?

359
00:15:41,870 --> 00:15:42,870
Fine, I won't drink then.

360
00:15:42,870 --> 00:15:43,390
What's with this?

361
00:15:43,390 --> 00:15:44,720
Are you going to kill me?

362
00:15:46,210 --> 00:15:47,510
That day, I...

363
00:15:47,840 --> 00:15:48,150
Listen.

364
00:15:48,150 --> 00:15:49,880
Lay off the alcohol from now on.

365
00:15:50,870 --> 00:15:52,550
It's like smoking opium for you.

366
00:15:52,550 --> 00:15:54,200
What? Are you addicted?

367
00:15:56,790 --> 00:15:58,270
I thought I'd finish this half bottle,

368
00:15:58,270 --> 00:15:58,840
and then I'd stop.

369
00:15:58,840 --> 00:16:00,020
Don't even drink that half bottle.

370
00:16:00,020 --> 00:16:00,930
What? Are you deaf?

371
00:16:00,930 --> 00:16:01,930
You won't listen?

372
00:16:02,490 --> 00:16:04,620
I won't drink it. I'm throwing it away.

373
00:16:06,390 --> 00:16:07,990
We're all on suspension now—

374
00:16:08,020 --> 00:16:10,620
even if I wanted to drink,
I couldn't afford it.

375
00:16:11,320 --> 00:16:12,270
This is on me too.

376
00:16:13,780 --> 00:16:16,040
If I hadn't gone out looking for that job,

377
00:16:16,150 --> 00:16:17,590
none of you would be caught up in this.

378
00:16:17,590 --> 00:16:19,450
What does this have to do with you?

379
00:16:19,480 --> 00:16:20,870
You led us to make money.

380
00:16:20,900 --> 00:16:22,100
We need to celebrate.

381
00:16:22,600 --> 00:16:23,240
It's fine.

382
00:16:24,870 --> 00:16:27,270
The Long March was much harder than this.

383
00:16:27,720 --> 00:16:29,390
We've just taken the first step.

384
00:16:29,390 --> 00:16:31,440
Why are you wilting
at the first sign of trouble?

385
00:16:31,440 --> 00:16:32,030
That won't do.

386
00:16:32,030 --> 00:16:33,600
That's not what a man does.

387
00:16:40,030 --> 00:16:41,050
Is the pot boiling?

388
00:16:41,050 --> 00:16:41,910
It's been ages.

389
00:16:43,440 --> 00:16:45,770
As long as I have food,
you won't go hungry.

390
00:16:46,020 --> 00:16:46,550
Get to it.

391
00:16:49,390 --> 00:16:51,030
Cook more. I'm starving.

392
00:16:53,780 --> 00:16:55,890
[Zhuang Sen: King returns]

393
00:17:18,890 --> 00:17:19,440
Xiaoman.

394
00:17:23,829 --> 00:17:24,589
Look at you.

395
00:17:24,589 --> 00:17:26,210
Is this the return of the king?

396
00:17:26,210 --> 00:17:26,930
So what?

397
00:17:27,550 --> 00:17:29,030
I came back with the rain.

398
00:17:29,280 --> 00:17:29,850
Come on.

399
00:17:29,870 --> 00:17:31,190
Get inside. Let's go.

400
00:17:31,440 --> 00:17:32,900
-I'm hungry.
-Are you wet?

401
00:17:33,830 --> 00:17:34,920
It's pouring rain,

402
00:17:34,920 --> 00:17:36,160
why are you climbing through the window?

403
00:17:36,160 --> 00:17:37,760
Do you owe my neighbor money?

404
00:17:42,960 --> 00:17:44,490
How is it? Does it look nice?

405
00:17:45,110 --> 00:17:45,680
It looks nice.

406
00:17:45,680 --> 00:17:46,590
Do you remember

407
00:17:46,590 --> 00:17:48,110
when we were at that lecture,

408
00:17:48,110 --> 00:17:49,370
and Madame Dupont said

409
00:17:49,510 --> 00:17:50,550
you have to

410
00:17:50,550 --> 00:17:52,350
immerse yourself in art

411
00:17:52,750 --> 00:17:54,720
to truly appreciate its beauty?

412
00:17:55,260 --> 00:17:56,260
This trip

413
00:17:57,070 --> 00:17:58,480
really made me understand what she meant—

414
00:17:58,480 --> 00:18:00,480
it applies perfectly to architecture.

415
00:18:00,480 --> 00:18:02,270
When you're standing right underneath it,

416
00:18:02,270 --> 00:18:03,920
it feels completely different
from just looking at photos.

417
00:18:03,920 --> 00:18:06,180
You took so many photos of just one tower?

418
00:18:06,920 --> 00:18:08,120
This is Italy, right?

419
00:18:08,640 --> 00:18:10,350
Yeah. Didn't you go there too?

420
00:18:10,680 --> 00:18:11,960
That paradise town.

421
00:18:14,200 --> 00:18:15,680
But it's a pity there wasn't enough time.

422
00:18:15,680 --> 00:18:17,720
In France, I only visited Paris.

423
00:18:17,830 --> 00:18:19,680
I missed out on Marseille and Nice.

424
00:18:19,680 --> 00:18:22,720
A few more days would have been enough.

425
00:18:23,640 --> 00:18:24,680
For you,

426
00:18:25,120 --> 00:18:27,710
would a few more days really be enough?

427
00:18:31,330 --> 00:18:33,530
I guess that really wouldn't be enough.

428
00:18:37,350 --> 00:18:39,110
I wish I had superpowers.

429
00:18:39,550 --> 00:18:40,640
Like, during the day,

430
00:18:40,640 --> 00:18:43,680
I continue studying architectural design
in Tongzhou.

431
00:18:43,680 --> 00:18:44,310
And then at night,

432
00:18:44,310 --> 00:18:45,350
I close my eyes,

433
00:18:45,680 --> 00:18:46,550
and the dream begins.

434
00:18:46,550 --> 00:18:49,280
I dream of going to
Europe to audit classes there.

435
00:18:50,350 --> 00:18:52,310
If you can do it in reality,

436
00:18:53,160 --> 00:18:54,510
why dream about it?

437
00:18:58,310 --> 00:18:59,680
I've stayed in Beijing
for a good few years.

438
00:18:59,680 --> 00:19:00,140
Really?

439
00:19:01,030 --> 00:19:02,160
Come take a look.

440
00:19:02,590 --> 00:19:03,250
Take a look.

441
00:19:03,680 --> 00:19:05,210
New arrivals from Beijing.

442
00:19:05,830 --> 00:19:07,200
All European and American styles.

443
00:19:07,200 --> 00:19:08,550
Come and have a look.

444
00:19:10,880 --> 00:19:11,640
Xiaoman.

445
00:19:13,820 --> 00:19:14,730
Here!

446
00:19:15,050 --> 00:19:16,380
Look up here.

447
00:19:18,270 --> 00:19:19,800
Why are you squatting here?

448
00:19:19,880 --> 00:19:20,880
This is the stall.

449
00:19:21,890 --> 00:19:24,150
You said the shops in Tiecheng were here.

450
00:19:24,560 --> 00:19:25,230
Yeah.

451
00:19:29,960 --> 00:19:31,880
This is one of the busiest spots,

452
00:19:32,030 --> 00:19:33,090
prime real estate.

453
00:19:33,830 --> 00:19:34,550
Oh, come on.

454
00:19:34,550 --> 00:19:35,920
What is this supposed to be?

455
00:19:35,920 --> 00:19:37,050
Watches on sale.

456
00:19:37,270 --> 00:19:37,680
Aren't you

457
00:19:37,680 --> 00:19:39,440
basically street vending?

458
00:19:39,440 --> 00:19:40,670
If the inspectors show up,
you'll all be running.

459
00:19:40,670 --> 00:19:41,950
It's a legal business.

460
00:19:42,640 --> 00:19:43,880
Look. Night market.

461
00:19:45,240 --> 00:19:46,240
Don't worry about the number.

462
00:19:46,240 --> 00:19:47,200
You got a stall number,

463
00:19:47,200 --> 00:19:47,830
and it's 250.

464
00:19:47,830 --> 00:19:48,550
Look at you.

465
00:19:50,390 --> 00:19:52,950
I'm going to combine our names

466
00:19:53,800 --> 00:19:54,860
to make a shop name.

467
00:19:54,940 --> 00:19:56,580
Combine our names?

468
00:19:57,640 --> 00:19:58,440
Zhuang Sen.

469
00:20:00,070 --> 00:20:00,640
Okay.

470
00:20:02,240 --> 00:20:02,920
Zhuang...

471
00:20:03,680 --> 00:20:04,890
Zhuangman.

472
00:20:04,920 --> 00:20:06,520
It means filling the wallet.

473
00:20:06,750 --> 00:20:08,350
It means filling the wallet.

474
00:20:09,030 --> 00:20:10,240
That means getting rich.

475
00:20:10,240 --> 00:20:10,830
Yeah.

476
00:20:11,640 --> 00:20:12,440
Wait a minute.

477
00:20:12,720 --> 00:20:13,850
Where are you going?

478
00:20:14,110 --> 00:20:14,640
Sis.

479
00:20:15,400 --> 00:20:17,000
Do you have paint at home?

480
00:20:17,240 --> 00:20:17,680
Yes.

481
00:20:17,680 --> 00:20:18,310
Come here.

482
00:20:20,880 --> 00:20:22,000
Clocks are on sale.

483
00:20:23,720 --> 00:20:26,160
Zhuangman.

484
00:20:27,550 --> 00:20:29,030
Johnson. Man.

485
00:20:29,240 --> 00:20:30,000
J.M.

486
00:20:31,310 --> 00:20:31,920
for

487
00:20:34,880 --> 00:20:35,680
short.

488
00:20:36,240 --> 00:20:37,830
The new darling of the fashion world,

489
00:20:37,830 --> 00:20:40,680
J.M. is on the rise.

490
00:20:41,550 --> 00:20:42,070
Great.

491
00:20:43,370 --> 00:20:45,030
Why did you step on their sign?

492
00:20:45,510 --> 00:20:45,920
We're done for.

493
00:20:45,920 --> 00:20:47,030
Are you blind?

494
00:20:47,030 --> 00:20:47,480
We're done for.

495
00:20:47,480 --> 00:20:48,550
This... this is J.W.

496
00:20:48,550 --> 00:20:49,000
See?

497
00:20:49,640 --> 00:20:51,170
Alright, let's get to work.

498
00:20:51,880 --> 00:20:52,740
Let me tell you,

499
00:20:53,270 --> 00:20:54,960
if we want this business to work,

500
00:20:54,960 --> 00:20:56,750
we have to catch them by surprise.

501
00:20:56,750 --> 00:20:57,590
What do you mean, surprise?

502
00:20:57,590 --> 00:20:58,960
With the way you wrapped this,

503
00:20:58,960 --> 00:20:59,960
who can see what's inside?

504
00:20:59,960 --> 00:21:01,550
People are curious.

505
00:21:01,920 --> 00:21:03,030
When you wrap it like this,

506
00:21:03,030 --> 00:21:04,550
they'll want to take a peek

507
00:21:04,750 --> 00:21:06,010
to see what's for sale.

508
00:21:06,400 --> 00:21:07,830
That's how you get business.

509
00:21:07,830 --> 00:21:09,550
Lots of big shops in Beijing do this,

510
00:21:09,550 --> 00:21:10,680
and their business is booming.

511
00:21:10,680 --> 00:21:11,200
Really?

512
00:21:12,350 --> 00:21:14,480
Then how come no one has come in all day?

513
00:21:18,400 --> 00:21:20,260
It's the first day. There's time.

514
00:21:31,720 --> 00:21:33,250
How long has he been asleep?

515
00:21:33,270 --> 00:21:34,240
Are there still no customers?

516
00:21:34,240 --> 00:21:35,240
Are you dreaming?

517
00:21:37,510 --> 00:21:38,110
Call out to the crowd.

518
00:21:38,110 --> 00:21:39,970
Why are you unwrapping the cloth?

519
00:21:40,310 --> 00:21:41,160
I'm changing tactics.

520
00:21:41,160 --> 00:21:43,090
How many tricks do you pull in a day?

521
00:21:43,160 --> 00:21:45,550
Come on! Don't miss out!

522
00:21:46,480 --> 00:21:49,590
The Western favorite, JM Jeans.

523
00:21:49,880 --> 00:21:52,210
Top-notch goods from Beijing Wholesale.

524
00:21:52,800 --> 00:21:54,400
Hey girl, want to take a look?

525
00:21:54,640 --> 00:21:56,100
We have all the new styles.

526
00:21:56,610 --> 00:21:58,280
Oh, you sell clothes?

527
00:21:58,310 --> 00:22:00,240
I've already walked around here twice.

528
00:22:00,240 --> 00:22:01,300
I didn't even know.

529
00:22:01,550 --> 00:22:03,600
It's pitch black all around here.

530
00:22:03,620 --> 00:22:04,680
I can't see anything.

531
00:22:04,680 --> 00:22:05,720
How much is this?

532
00:22:06,360 --> 00:22:06,880
Miss,

533
00:22:09,200 --> 00:22:10,400
you have great taste.

534
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:12,510
This is the best stuff I picked

535
00:22:12,510 --> 00:22:14,440
from the Dongpi Market in Beijing.

536
00:22:14,830 --> 00:22:15,830
It's the only one.

537
00:22:16,200 --> 00:22:16,830
How much?

538
00:22:17,240 --> 00:22:18,030
320.

539
00:22:18,310 --> 00:22:19,110
That's too expensive.

540
00:22:19,110 --> 00:22:20,710
Other places sell it for 200.

541
00:22:20,850 --> 00:22:22,890
Alright, 300—I'll let you have it.

542
00:22:22,960 --> 00:22:23,960
Fine, 300.

543
00:22:26,870 --> 00:22:28,220
Quick, help me get a bag.

544
00:22:29,920 --> 00:22:33,010
JM jeans—the darling
of the European fashion scene,

545
00:22:33,030 --> 00:22:35,430
puts you right
at the cutting edge of style.

546
00:22:39,960 --> 00:22:40,960
Throw it up there.

547
00:22:46,270 --> 00:22:46,930
Let's ride.

548
00:22:47,200 --> 00:22:47,920
Put your back into it.

549
00:22:47,920 --> 00:22:49,850
Super tasty grilled chicken ribs!

550
00:22:51,800 --> 00:22:52,820
It really smells good.

551
00:22:52,820 --> 00:22:54,480
Do you think if I sold this stuff

552
00:22:54,480 --> 00:22:56,510
at our factory, it would sell well?

553
00:22:56,760 --> 00:22:57,440
Of course.

554
00:22:58,000 --> 00:22:59,030
People gotta eat.

555
00:22:59,550 --> 00:23:00,150
All right.

556
00:23:00,640 --> 00:23:01,790
I'll come try some tomorrow.

557
00:23:01,790 --> 00:23:02,430
Okay. Take care.

558
00:23:02,430 --> 00:23:03,150
Let's go.

559
00:23:06,070 --> 00:23:06,790
Here we go.

560
00:23:07,240 --> 00:23:08,200
Quick, move aside. It's hot.

561
00:23:08,200 --> 00:23:09,240
Hurry up. Come on.

562
00:23:10,750 --> 00:23:11,680
Touch your ears. Quick.

563
00:23:11,680 --> 00:23:12,350
Let me taste it.

564
00:23:12,350 --> 00:23:13,200
Get up first.

565
00:23:15,070 --> 00:23:16,000
Come on, Mentor.

566
00:23:16,310 --> 00:23:16,920
Come on.

567
00:23:17,120 --> 00:23:17,710
Come on.

568
00:23:19,640 --> 00:23:20,680
This is my new recipe—

569
00:23:20,680 --> 00:23:22,280
Xinjiang Big Plate Chicken.

570
00:23:22,460 --> 00:23:23,060
Dig in.

571
00:23:23,120 --> 00:23:23,760
Come on.

572
00:23:24,370 --> 00:23:26,840
Mentor, this isn't
Xinjiang Big Plate Chicken.

573
00:23:26,840 --> 00:23:29,330
It's clearly
Xinjiang Big Plate Chicken Ribs.

574
00:23:29,330 --> 00:23:31,720
I wonder how long
you'll be waiting for work.

575
00:23:31,720 --> 00:23:32,590
If you don't go back soon,

576
00:23:32,590 --> 00:23:34,370
we won't even be able
to afford chicken ribs.

577
00:23:34,370 --> 00:23:35,700
Go get the wine glasses.

578
00:23:40,510 --> 00:23:41,160
Xiaoman.

579
00:23:41,790 --> 00:23:43,390
You keep running to the city.

580
00:23:43,590 --> 00:23:45,320
Keep an eye out for your mentor.

581
00:23:45,590 --> 00:23:47,390
See if there's any work he can do.

582
00:23:47,400 --> 00:23:48,600
Working in Tiecheng?

583
00:23:48,880 --> 00:23:50,540
There's plenty of work there.

584
00:23:50,830 --> 00:23:51,440
My mentor went to...

585
00:23:51,440 --> 00:23:52,170
Let me think.

586
00:23:52,880 --> 00:23:54,340
We'll talk about it later.

587
00:23:54,580 --> 00:23:55,640
By the way, Mentor,

588
00:23:56,160 --> 00:23:58,270
you know what's everywhere
in Tiecheng now?

589
00:23:58,270 --> 00:24:00,110
Grilled chicken rib stalls.

590
00:24:01,030 --> 00:24:02,880
Grilled, fried, cold tossed,

591
00:24:02,960 --> 00:24:04,550
sweet-and-sour, spicy—

592
00:24:04,640 --> 00:24:05,790
all kinds.

593
00:24:05,790 --> 00:24:06,720
They are so popular.

594
00:24:06,720 --> 00:24:07,480
Really?

595
00:24:07,480 --> 00:24:08,790
For real. With my mentor's skills,

596
00:24:08,790 --> 00:24:10,050
he'd wipe them all out.

597
00:24:11,200 --> 00:24:11,800
Is that so?

598
00:24:16,640 --> 00:24:17,440
Our grills

599
00:24:17,690 --> 00:24:19,220
are made of real materials.

600
00:24:19,810 --> 00:24:20,570
I can tell.

601
00:24:22,720 --> 00:24:23,720
These steel plates are welded,

602
00:24:23,720 --> 00:24:24,310
right?

603
00:24:25,410 --> 00:24:27,470
Isn't this rack just bent steel wire?

604
00:24:27,560 --> 00:24:28,160
Yes.

605
00:24:29,310 --> 00:24:30,790
So this grill—

606
00:24:30,790 --> 00:24:31,950
how much are you selling it for?

607
00:24:31,950 --> 00:24:32,800
200 a set.

608
00:24:33,830 --> 00:24:35,680
It comes with two extra grates,

609
00:24:36,590 --> 00:24:38,540
and a replacement grate for free.

610
00:24:39,510 --> 00:24:40,310
200, huh?

611
00:24:40,400 --> 00:24:40,880
Yes.

612
00:24:42,780 --> 00:24:44,350
What's this for?

613
00:24:44,480 --> 00:24:45,070
This one?

614
00:24:45,130 --> 00:24:46,520
280, all-in-one.

615
00:24:46,660 --> 00:24:48,000
If the city inspectors show up,

616
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:49,660
you can hop on the bike and run.

617
00:24:49,840 --> 00:24:50,840
City inspectors?

618
00:24:51,440 --> 00:24:54,120
I'm grilling in my own factory —
they're gonna bust me?

619
00:24:54,120 --> 00:24:56,380
If they try,
I'll make them buy me dinner.

620
00:24:57,280 --> 00:25:00,280
Brother, you're from
the East Chemical Plant, right?

621
00:25:04,110 --> 00:25:04,830
Me?

622
00:25:04,850 --> 00:25:06,760
I'm from Chaoyang Machinery Plant
in the east.

623
00:25:06,760 --> 00:25:08,310
Then we're practically sister units.

624
00:25:08,310 --> 00:25:09,110
That's right.

625
00:25:09,520 --> 00:25:11,760
So you don't need to buy a grill from me.

626
00:25:11,790 --> 00:25:12,930
No, I have to buy it.

627
00:25:13,240 --> 00:25:14,430
How much? 200, right?

628
00:25:14,430 --> 00:25:15,690
I'll take this big one.

629
00:25:21,410 --> 00:25:22,270
I didn't bring enough money....

630
00:25:22,270 --> 00:25:22,960
Brother.

631
00:25:24,790 --> 00:25:25,550
Brother,

632
00:25:26,310 --> 00:25:26,920
you...

633
00:25:26,920 --> 00:25:28,120
don't bother paying.

634
00:25:30,630 --> 00:25:32,670
From the start,

635
00:25:33,440 --> 00:25:35,700
you just wanted to
weld a grill yourself,

636
00:25:35,710 --> 00:25:36,370
didn't you?

637
00:25:37,830 --> 00:25:39,360
Poverty stifles ambition.

638
00:25:40,440 --> 00:25:43,100
But I ran into you—
see, we're sister factories.

639
00:25:44,800 --> 00:25:46,480
Wait here. I'll go back and get the money.

640
00:25:46,480 --> 00:25:47,590
I live close by.
I'll come back and buy it.

641
00:25:47,590 --> 00:25:48,920
I'll definitely buy it.

642
00:25:49,610 --> 00:25:51,850
It must be fate that we met.

643
00:25:51,880 --> 00:25:53,080
If you really want it,

644
00:25:53,680 --> 00:25:54,680
take it for 50 yuan.

645
00:25:54,680 --> 00:25:55,510
-Take it.
-Forget it.

646
00:25:55,510 --> 00:25:56,960
50? That doesn't even cover the materials.

647
00:25:56,960 --> 00:25:58,160
That won't do. No way.

648
00:25:58,700 --> 00:26:00,660
What material costs are you talking about?

649
00:26:00,660 --> 00:26:03,260
I just picked up
some steel plates and old wire.

650
00:26:03,470 --> 00:26:04,230
50 yuan.

651
00:26:05,010 --> 00:26:06,250
Don't argue with me.

652
00:26:06,720 --> 00:26:07,580
Did you hear me?

653
00:26:08,950 --> 00:26:09,460
Okay.

654
00:26:13,110 --> 00:26:14,240
Thank you.

655
00:26:15,190 --> 00:26:16,510
Isn't this burnt?

656
00:26:17,310 --> 00:26:18,920
Let me give you some pointers.

657
00:26:18,920 --> 00:26:20,030
Stop bothering us.

658
00:26:20,030 --> 00:26:21,200
Step aside. You're in the way.

659
00:26:21,200 --> 00:26:21,830
Get out.

660
00:26:22,160 --> 00:26:23,220
Mentor, come here.

661
00:26:23,510 --> 00:26:25,270
More? I haven't even
figured these two out.

662
00:26:25,270 --> 00:26:26,160
Those two are burnt.

663
00:26:26,160 --> 00:26:27,090
Get two new ones.

664
00:26:27,200 --> 00:26:27,790
It's so spicy.

665
00:26:27,790 --> 00:26:28,920
What are you doing?

666
00:26:29,190 --> 00:26:29,920
Mr. Xia is here.

667
00:26:29,920 --> 00:26:31,650
Who grills this stuff indoors?

668
00:26:32,000 --> 00:26:33,630
Do you know how to handle this?

669
00:26:33,630 --> 00:26:34,430
Oh my God.

670
00:26:35,720 --> 00:26:37,110
Who pours oil like that?

671
00:26:37,110 --> 00:26:38,500
You're frying the chicken ribs.

672
00:26:38,500 --> 00:26:39,230
Are these...

673
00:26:39,440 --> 00:26:40,640
Are you grilling chicken ribs,

674
00:26:40,640 --> 00:26:42,110
or are you grilling charcoal?

675
00:26:42,110 --> 00:26:43,720
Why is it so black?

676
00:26:43,720 --> 00:26:44,270
Throw it away.

677
00:26:44,270 --> 00:26:45,030
This one is ruined.

678
00:26:45,030 --> 00:26:46,110
Throw it away.

679
00:26:46,110 --> 00:26:47,910
Grill that one. Here's a new one.

680
00:26:48,110 --> 00:26:49,110
Even if I haven't grilled this before,

681
00:26:49,110 --> 00:26:51,350
and even if I've never eaten pork,

682
00:26:51,350 --> 00:26:53,350
I've seen a barbecue.

683
00:26:53,860 --> 00:26:55,790
Did you marinate the chicken ribs?

684
00:26:55,950 --> 00:26:57,550
No. Aren't they grilled raw?

685
00:26:57,880 --> 00:26:58,880
You didn't marinate them?

686
00:26:58,880 --> 00:26:59,900
Do you have scallions, ginger, and garlic?

687
00:26:59,900 --> 00:27:00,960
Soak them in water.

688
00:27:01,040 --> 00:27:02,270
And Sichuan peppercorns.

689
00:27:02,270 --> 00:27:03,790
Peppercorn water.
Soak the peppercorns too.

690
00:27:03,790 --> 00:27:06,000
Is that exhaust fan just for decoration?

691
00:27:06,000 --> 00:27:06,880
It's not on.

692
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:08,400
Don't turn it on, Mentor.

693
00:27:08,480 --> 00:27:09,410
Don't turn it on.

694
00:27:09,440 --> 00:27:10,400
The blades are on backward.

695
00:27:10,400 --> 00:27:11,030
It's blowing inward.

696
00:27:11,030 --> 00:27:12,090
Turn it off, quick.

697
00:27:12,160 --> 00:27:13,560
The blades are backward.

698
00:27:16,190 --> 00:27:18,400
This batch was grilled
under Xia's guidance—

699
00:27:18,400 --> 00:27:19,200
and this one,

700
00:27:19,960 --> 00:27:20,830
this is the one I did.

701
00:27:20,830 --> 00:27:22,240
Have a taste. Give me some feedback.

702
00:27:22,240 --> 00:27:23,040
It looks okay.

703
00:27:23,590 --> 00:27:24,310
I...

704
00:27:24,310 --> 00:27:25,310
I'll take a bite, Mentor.

705
00:27:25,310 --> 00:27:26,420
I'm an expert at eating.

706
00:27:26,420 --> 00:27:27,830
Come on.

707
00:27:27,860 --> 00:27:29,010
Cut the ribbon.

708
00:27:31,660 --> 00:27:32,370
How is it?

709
00:27:34,000 --> 00:27:35,460
It's flavorful this time.

710
00:27:35,830 --> 00:27:36,830
Just a few spots

711
00:27:36,830 --> 00:27:37,890
are a little burnt.

712
00:27:38,240 --> 00:27:39,660
I was worried it might be undercooked;

713
00:27:39,660 --> 00:27:40,590
I'm still a bit rusty.

714
00:27:40,590 --> 00:27:41,550
It's pretty good.

715
00:27:41,550 --> 00:27:42,640
Exactly. It's good.

716
00:27:42,640 --> 00:27:43,200
It's good.

717
00:27:43,200 --> 00:27:44,400
Actually, the biggest mistake

718
00:27:44,400 --> 00:27:46,330
was not marinating it beforehand.

719
00:27:46,440 --> 00:27:47,310
Before roasting the chicken ribs,

720
00:27:47,310 --> 00:27:48,640
you have to marinate them

721
00:27:48,640 --> 00:27:49,880
for 20 or 30 minutes.

722
00:27:49,880 --> 00:27:51,000
That way, it's flavorful,

723
00:27:51,000 --> 00:27:52,400
and it won't burn easily.

724
00:27:52,680 --> 00:27:53,400
It smells good.

725
00:27:53,400 --> 00:27:53,960
I'll know for next time.

726
00:27:53,960 --> 00:27:54,440
I'll do it next time.

727
00:27:54,440 --> 00:27:55,240
Okay. I get it now.

728
00:27:55,240 --> 00:27:55,920
Come on.

729
00:27:55,920 --> 00:27:57,090
Taste your own cooking.

730
00:27:57,090 --> 00:27:57,680
It smells so good.

731
00:27:57,680 --> 00:27:58,740
It's really tasty.

732
00:27:59,190 --> 00:27:59,780
Mr. Ding,

733
00:27:59,990 --> 00:28:00,750
I just saw

734
00:28:00,830 --> 00:28:01,790
that your family

735
00:28:01,790 --> 00:28:03,330
grows your own chilies and leeks.

736
00:28:03,330 --> 00:28:03,930
You bet.

737
00:28:04,420 --> 00:28:05,310
These things

738
00:28:05,330 --> 00:28:07,600
can all be grilled with the chicken racks.

739
00:28:07,600 --> 00:28:08,270
Really?

740
00:28:08,300 --> 00:28:09,960
It's a mix of meat and veggies—

741
00:28:10,510 --> 00:28:12,230
nutritious and delicious.

742
00:28:12,920 --> 00:28:14,800
Xia, that's some fancy language.

743
00:28:15,060 --> 00:28:15,620
Mr. Ding,

744
00:28:16,500 --> 00:28:17,640
when you open your stall,

745
00:28:17,640 --> 00:28:18,570
you must tell me.

746
00:28:18,860 --> 00:28:20,260
I'll come to support you.

747
00:28:20,580 --> 00:28:22,310
And mooch some food and drinks.

748
00:28:24,190 --> 00:28:25,590
What stall?

749
00:28:26,640 --> 00:28:27,510
I'm just grilling for fun.

750
00:28:27,510 --> 00:28:28,310
No stall.

751
00:28:30,550 --> 00:28:31,440
It's delicious.

752
00:28:31,440 --> 00:28:33,240
Especially delicious, Mentor.

753
00:28:33,600 --> 00:28:34,470
What's wrong?

754
00:28:35,550 --> 00:28:37,510
Don't you want to make money?

755
00:28:37,510 --> 00:28:40,040
Or do you think setting up
a stall is shameful?

756
00:28:40,720 --> 00:28:42,450
It's not... It's not like that.

757
00:28:43,690 --> 00:28:46,450
Mr. Ding, with the courage
of this alcohol today,

758
00:28:46,750 --> 00:28:47,880
I'll speak frankly.

759
00:28:48,440 --> 00:28:50,160
Here's the thing. I think

760
00:28:50,360 --> 00:28:51,700
earning money with our own skills

761
00:28:51,700 --> 00:28:52,730
isn't shameful.

762
00:28:53,710 --> 00:28:54,840
Take me for example.

763
00:28:54,960 --> 00:28:57,030
I started driving a taxi
after I got laid off.

764
00:28:57,030 --> 00:28:58,830
Is it shameful?

765
00:29:01,160 --> 00:29:02,160
It is a bit shameful.

766
00:29:02,160 --> 00:29:03,810
At least I thought so at the beginning.

767
00:29:03,810 --> 00:29:05,330
But later, I stopped caring.

768
00:29:05,330 --> 00:29:07,370
If people want to gossip, let them.

769
00:29:08,360 --> 00:29:09,720
If gossip could put food on the table,

770
00:29:09,720 --> 00:29:10,590
I'd take it all.

771
00:29:14,640 --> 00:29:15,920
I know, Mr. Ding.

772
00:29:16,640 --> 00:29:18,590
You're a war hero—

773
00:29:18,590 --> 00:29:20,110
the pride of our factory.

774
00:29:21,800 --> 00:29:25,490
But this is what life is now.

775
00:29:25,510 --> 00:29:27,670
We have to look out for ourselves
and keep moving forward.

776
00:29:27,670 --> 00:29:28,350
Yes, yes.

777
00:29:28,640 --> 00:29:30,200
-Mr. Xia, don't say that.
-Moving forward.

778
00:29:30,200 --> 00:29:30,750
Exactly.

779
00:29:31,860 --> 00:29:33,060
What are we afraid of?

780
00:29:33,110 --> 00:29:33,590
Right?

781
00:29:34,310 --> 00:29:37,640
Besides, Mentor's hands
used to hold a gun.

782
00:29:38,030 --> 00:29:39,790
Holding two skewers now
is a piece of cake for him.

783
00:29:39,790 --> 00:29:40,650
-Yeah.
-Right?

784
00:29:43,790 --> 00:29:44,350
Cheers.

785
00:29:44,750 --> 00:29:45,240
Cheers.

786
00:29:45,240 --> 00:29:45,700
Come on.

787
00:29:45,830 --> 00:29:46,510
I said cheers, but...

788
00:29:46,510 --> 00:29:47,270
Drink slowly.

789
00:29:47,270 --> 00:29:48,510
You just gulped down a huge mouthful.

790
00:29:48,510 --> 00:29:49,510
You guys eat. I'll grill some more.

791
00:29:49,510 --> 00:29:50,350
Okay. Come on.

792
00:29:50,440 --> 00:29:51,200
Drink up.

793
00:29:51,550 --> 00:29:52,070
Come on.

794
00:29:53,590 --> 00:29:54,450
Let me tell you.

795
00:29:54,980 --> 00:29:57,500
I drive my taxi all over the place,

796
00:29:57,880 --> 00:29:59,480
running around everywhere.

797
00:29:59,550 --> 00:30:00,710
I eat wherever I go.

798
00:30:00,960 --> 00:30:02,710
I've noticed that
with barbecue these days,

799
00:30:02,710 --> 00:30:05,560
as long as it's something
you can throw on a grate,

800
00:30:05,580 --> 00:30:06,440
you can sell it,

801
00:30:06,450 --> 00:30:07,710
and it actually tastes pretty good.

802
00:30:07,710 --> 00:30:08,510
So

803
00:30:08,720 --> 00:30:10,830
we could just put all of it on the menu.

804
00:30:11,060 --> 00:30:13,230
Even those chicken tails
you guys toss on skewers—

805
00:30:13,230 --> 00:30:15,360
they'd sell too.

806
00:30:16,160 --> 00:30:18,030
Come on, Mr. Xia, you're messing with me.

807
00:30:18,030 --> 00:30:20,000
Who eats chicken butts?

808
00:30:20,360 --> 00:30:21,200
Look at you.

809
00:30:28,880 --> 00:30:30,810
Come on, for your aunt, you have to...

810
00:30:30,810 --> 00:30:31,610
This thing...

811
00:30:32,070 --> 00:30:32,680
It's too choking.

812
00:30:32,680 --> 00:30:33,590
-Yes. Yes.
-It's so annoying.

813
00:30:33,590 --> 00:30:34,440
This...

814
00:30:34,800 --> 00:30:36,310
Did you put chili on it just now?

815
00:30:36,310 --> 00:30:36,720
No, no.

816
00:30:36,720 --> 00:30:39,120
Then the charcoal quality isn't very good.

817
00:30:40,720 --> 00:30:41,830
Let me do it for a while, Mentor.

818
00:30:41,830 --> 00:30:43,230
No need. Go do your thing.

819
00:30:43,330 --> 00:30:43,890
Go.

820
00:30:46,290 --> 00:30:46,970
Okay.

821
00:31:12,090 --> 00:31:13,030
What would you like?

822
00:31:13,030 --> 00:31:13,960
What do you have?

823
00:31:14,030 --> 00:31:15,640
Our specialties are chicken ribs,
meat skewers.

824
00:31:15,640 --> 00:31:16,930
and all kinds of vegetables.

825
00:31:16,930 --> 00:31:18,330
Give me two beef skewers.

826
00:31:18,650 --> 00:31:20,070
Just two skewers?

827
00:31:20,240 --> 00:31:21,480
What? Too few to grill?

828
00:31:21,480 --> 00:31:22,440
No, I'll grill them.

829
00:31:22,440 --> 00:31:23,440
If you grill them, I won't eat them.

830
00:31:23,440 --> 00:31:24,510
No, brother. I'll grill them right away.

831
00:31:24,510 --> 00:31:26,200
It's on the grill.

832
00:31:27,050 --> 00:31:27,580
Look.

833
00:31:29,200 --> 00:31:31,160
Mr. Ding, what are you doing there?

834
00:31:31,160 --> 00:31:33,070
You said you were fixing the door,

835
00:31:33,070 --> 00:31:35,200
but you've stripped the screws halfway in.

836
00:31:35,200 --> 00:31:36,440
What are you doing?

837
00:31:37,970 --> 00:31:39,570
You're throwing things now?

838
00:31:42,060 --> 00:31:43,140
I'll eat it myself.

839
00:31:43,170 --> 00:31:44,070
You grill it.

840
00:31:44,190 --> 00:31:45,320
If you won't grill it

841
00:31:45,350 --> 00:31:46,440
and don't let the smoke out,

842
00:31:46,440 --> 00:31:46,790
no one will know

843
00:31:46,790 --> 00:31:47,880
what you're doing with this stuff.

844
00:31:47,880 --> 00:31:48,270
Yeah.

845
00:31:48,270 --> 00:31:50,130
Wait. Why are you working so hard today?

846
00:31:50,130 --> 00:31:51,760
When am I not hard-working?

847
00:31:52,200 --> 00:31:53,110
It's mainly because today,

848
00:31:53,110 --> 00:31:54,110
Xiaoman specifically told me

849
00:31:54,110 --> 00:31:55,310
to be more diligent.

850
00:31:55,640 --> 00:31:57,000
He said you wouldn't be proactive,

851
00:31:57,000 --> 00:31:58,520
and look at you, you're actually there

852
00:31:58,520 --> 00:31:59,640
working your butt off.

853
00:31:59,640 --> 00:32:00,590
Look at you.

854
00:32:01,200 --> 00:32:02,240
Where is Xiaoman?

855
00:32:02,440 --> 00:32:03,440
Xiaoman said

856
00:32:03,440 --> 00:32:06,080
he's going to get me
some high-quality charcoal.

857
00:32:06,080 --> 00:32:07,070
He called it "restocking ammo."

858
00:32:07,070 --> 00:32:09,130
Making this barbecue feel like a war.

859
00:32:10,270 --> 00:32:12,480
If you were at war,
it'd be more intense than this.

860
00:32:12,480 --> 00:32:13,960
Look at how slow you are.

861
00:32:13,960 --> 00:32:15,680
You wouldn't be this slow in a war.

862
00:32:15,680 --> 00:32:16,530
That's right.

863
00:32:21,920 --> 00:32:22,310
Shi.

864
00:32:22,310 --> 00:32:23,200
What are you doing with that?

865
00:32:23,200 --> 00:32:24,110
Look at what I made.

866
00:32:24,110 --> 00:32:24,720
How is it?

867
00:32:25,110 --> 00:32:25,840
Take it back.

868
00:32:25,880 --> 00:32:26,480
Why take it back?

869
00:32:26,480 --> 00:32:27,270
Hang it up.

870
00:32:27,270 --> 00:32:28,240
It stands out too much.

871
00:32:28,240 --> 00:32:28,840
Hang it up.

872
00:32:28,920 --> 00:32:29,510
Hang it up.

873
00:32:29,510 --> 00:32:30,350
Look, hang it up. Come on.

874
00:32:30,350 --> 00:32:31,310
It looks way more impressive.

875
00:32:31,310 --> 00:32:32,240
Hang it up.

876
00:32:32,970 --> 00:32:33,700
Look at that.

877
00:32:34,020 --> 00:32:35,320
It looks way more impressive.

878
00:32:35,320 --> 00:32:35,930
Isn't it?

879
00:32:36,680 --> 00:32:37,880
Look, stretch it out.

880
00:32:38,340 --> 00:32:38,970
Look.

881
00:32:38,790 --> 00:32:42,400
[Ding's Chicken Ribs]

882
00:32:40,270 --> 00:32:41,160
Ding.

883
00:32:41,270 --> 00:32:42,640
Ding's Grilled Chicken Ribs.

884
00:32:42,640 --> 00:32:45,100
-Lower your voice.
-You've got real skills.

885
00:32:46,720 --> 00:32:47,250
How is it?

886
00:32:47,480 --> 00:32:48,000
It's great.

887
00:32:48,000 --> 00:32:49,000
It's really good.

888
00:32:49,270 --> 00:32:50,200
I'm telling you.

889
00:32:50,480 --> 00:32:51,680
Come on, let's eat.

890
00:32:51,680 --> 00:32:53,310
Ding's Grilled Chicken Ribs.

891
00:32:53,310 --> 00:32:54,830
-Have some roast chicken ribs.
-Chicken ribs.

892
00:32:54,830 --> 00:32:55,720
Delicious chicken ribs.

893
00:32:55,720 --> 00:32:56,830
Have a taste.

894
00:32:56,830 --> 00:32:58,590
Wait, Mentor.
It's Ding's Grilled Chicken Ribs,

895
00:32:58,590 --> 00:33:00,200
but Brother Shi is grilling here.

896
00:33:00,200 --> 00:33:01,240
That's not right.

897
00:33:03,790 --> 00:33:04,440
Uncle Xia and Aunt Xia.

898
00:33:04,440 --> 00:33:05,240
What's going on here?

899
00:33:05,240 --> 00:33:06,300
What are you doing?

900
00:33:07,110 --> 00:33:08,440
Look, look. How is it?

901
00:33:08,750 --> 00:33:09,240
Our

902
00:33:09,260 --> 00:33:11,670
Ding's Grilled Chicken Ribs.

903
00:33:11,960 --> 00:33:12,960
That's not right.

904
00:33:13,400 --> 00:33:15,550
This is Ding's Grilled Chicken Ribs.

905
00:33:15,550 --> 00:33:17,550
Where is Ding?

906
00:33:18,200 --> 00:33:18,720
Ding!

907
00:33:19,200 --> 00:33:20,270
Is Ding here?

908
00:33:20,440 --> 00:33:21,560
Where did Ding go?

909
00:33:21,590 --> 00:33:22,070
Exactly.

910
00:33:22,070 --> 00:33:22,830
Where did Ding go?

911
00:33:22,830 --> 00:33:23,070
Ding!

912
00:33:23,070 --> 00:33:24,480
-Where is Ding?
-What are you doing?

913
00:33:24,480 --> 00:33:25,510
Where is Ding?

914
00:33:25,790 --> 00:33:26,550
Hurry up and get up.

915
00:33:26,550 --> 00:33:30,030
Since we've set up, let's grill.

916
00:33:30,030 --> 00:33:31,110
Just shout it out.

917
00:33:31,110 --> 00:33:32,970
-Come on. Two skewers.
-Hurry up.

918
00:33:33,210 --> 00:33:34,880
What are you two doing here?
Making a mess?

919
00:33:34,880 --> 00:33:35,680
We're here to taste your cooking.

920
00:33:35,680 --> 00:33:36,270
We're craving it.

921
00:33:36,270 --> 00:33:37,440
You practiced so well at home,

922
00:33:37,440 --> 00:33:38,310
but now you're silent.

923
00:33:38,310 --> 00:33:39,070
Whose...

924
00:33:40,160 --> 00:33:41,690
Whose stall smells so good?

925
00:33:41,910 --> 00:33:44,510
It turns out
it's Ding's Grilled Chicken Ribs.

926
00:33:44,880 --> 00:33:45,480
My throat.

927
00:33:45,500 --> 00:33:47,160
Ding's Grilled Chicken Ribs.

928
00:33:47,350 --> 00:33:48,830
Ding's Grilled Chicken Ribs.

929
00:33:48,830 --> 00:33:49,790
You two...

930
00:33:50,110 --> 00:33:51,000
Come in if you want to eat.

931
00:33:51,000 --> 00:33:53,790
If you keep howling,
get the hell out. Do you hear me?

932
00:33:53,790 --> 00:33:55,310
Xiaoman asked me to come be a shill.

933
00:33:55,310 --> 00:33:57,590
Mr. and Mrs. Wang Dongdong,
please come in.

934
00:33:57,590 --> 00:33:58,000
Hurry up.

935
00:33:58,000 --> 00:33:59,240
I'm a passerby now.

936
00:33:59,240 --> 00:34:00,850
Passerby couple, please come in.

937
00:34:00,850 --> 00:34:02,850
Here! Chicken ribs!

938
00:34:02,880 --> 00:34:04,280
Two? Please come inside.

939
00:34:23,790 --> 00:34:27,530
How are the preparations for your study
abroad materials coming along?

940
00:34:27,530 --> 00:34:28,610
I'm working on it.

941
00:34:29,800 --> 00:34:31,630
Dad, why do you keep rushing me?

942
00:34:31,630 --> 00:34:33,110
Do you want me to go abroad that badly?

943
00:34:33,110 --> 00:34:34,639
Won't you miss me if I leave?

944
00:34:37,230 --> 00:34:39,230
It's not like
we won't see each other again.

945
00:34:39,230 --> 00:34:40,030
Besides,

946
00:34:40,219 --> 00:34:42,610
it's fine if you want to stay abroad.

947
00:34:42,670 --> 00:34:44,590
Your mom and I are retired now anyway,

948
00:34:44,590 --> 00:34:46,650
so we can go keep you company anytime.

949
00:34:48,239 --> 00:34:49,840
So you won't let me come back?

950
00:34:50,480 --> 00:34:51,480
What does that mean?

951
00:34:51,480 --> 00:34:52,590
There's more to this.

952
00:34:52,590 --> 00:34:53,650
It's a conspiracy.

953
00:34:55,810 --> 00:34:57,520
There's no conspiracy.

954
00:34:57,830 --> 00:34:59,030
This is your destiny.

955
00:34:59,570 --> 00:35:02,260
Don't you like Magellan the most?

956
00:35:02,630 --> 00:35:05,590
Magellan is destined to roam the world.

957
00:35:08,480 --> 00:35:10,840
So you want me to roam the world?

958
00:35:11,800 --> 00:35:12,880
I think you just don't want

959
00:35:12,880 --> 00:35:14,440
me to be with Xiaoman.

960
00:35:15,800 --> 00:35:18,030
Do you think I'm some

961
00:35:18,030 --> 00:35:19,800
feudal parent from the old society?

962
00:35:19,800 --> 00:35:21,400
Even if I wanted to break you up,

963
00:35:21,400 --> 00:35:22,590
could I?

964
00:35:23,480 --> 00:35:24,840
But now that you mention it,

965
00:35:24,840 --> 00:35:25,770
I actually think

966
00:35:26,640 --> 00:35:30,170
you don't seem to have much confidence
in your future together.

967
00:35:30,680 --> 00:35:31,740
But the reality is,

968
00:35:32,030 --> 00:35:33,760
he is at the East Chemical Plant,

969
00:35:33,760 --> 00:35:35,090
and you are in Shanghai.

970
00:35:35,220 --> 00:35:36,780
If you two want to meet,

971
00:35:37,280 --> 00:35:39,280
you can still do it with some effort.

972
00:35:39,510 --> 00:35:40,960
But once you go abroad,

973
00:35:41,670 --> 00:35:43,470
you really will be worlds apart.

974
00:35:46,070 --> 00:35:47,070
Who says that?

975
00:35:48,070 --> 00:35:49,280
We agreed.

976
00:35:49,590 --> 00:35:52,130
After I graduate from college,
we're going to move forward together.

977
00:35:52,130 --> 00:35:52,820
Good.

978
00:35:52,850 --> 00:35:54,780
Then you should be more confident,

979
00:35:54,800 --> 00:35:55,550
right?

980
00:35:55,670 --> 00:35:57,030
You should stride forward boldly

981
00:35:57,030 --> 00:35:58,840
without looking back,

982
00:35:59,280 --> 00:36:01,140
and see if he can catch up with you.

983
00:36:02,120 --> 00:36:02,930
He can.

984
00:36:03,840 --> 00:36:05,640
He told me to keep walking ahead.

985
00:36:06,570 --> 00:36:08,530
He'd catch up.

986
00:36:09,000 --> 00:36:09,920
Great.

987
00:36:10,480 --> 00:36:12,280
Then what are you worried about?

988
00:36:14,220 --> 00:36:15,150
I'm not worried.

989
00:36:30,000 --> 00:36:31,000
Keep it, Mr. Ding.

990
00:36:31,300 --> 00:36:32,230
I'm telling you,

991
00:36:32,230 --> 00:36:33,840
put it back in whichever pocket
you took it from.

992
00:36:33,840 --> 00:36:34,440
Do you hear me?

993
00:36:34,440 --> 00:36:35,350
What are you doing?

994
00:36:35,350 --> 00:36:36,410
What are you doing?

995
00:36:37,090 --> 00:36:37,860
Look at me.

996
00:36:38,320 --> 00:36:39,880
I don't have anywhere to spend money.

997
00:36:39,880 --> 00:36:40,320
Right?

998
00:36:40,320 --> 00:36:41,280
I can't afford expensive things,

999
00:36:41,280 --> 00:36:42,940
and I don't need cheap things.

1000
00:36:43,190 --> 00:36:44,590
You and Mrs. Ding need money right now.

1001
00:36:44,590 --> 00:36:45,510
Why are you being so polite with me?

1002
00:36:45,510 --> 00:36:46,920
Why would I... How could I

1003
00:36:47,710 --> 00:36:48,710
take your money?

1004
00:36:49,190 --> 00:36:50,050
Have I no shame?

1005
00:36:50,160 --> 00:36:52,190
-What are you talking about?
-I'm not at that point yet.

1006
00:36:52,190 --> 00:36:54,080
What kind of talk is that?
What's wrong with taking my money?

1007
00:36:54,080 --> 00:36:56,210
I eat and drink at your place every day—

1008
00:36:56,240 --> 00:36:58,400
what's wrong with me
giving you some money?

1009
00:36:58,400 --> 00:36:58,920
Right?

1010
00:36:59,190 --> 00:37:01,320
Look how tired Mrs. Ding is. Just look.

1011
00:37:01,810 --> 00:37:03,020
Bring four beers.

1012
00:37:03,500 --> 00:37:04,140
Okay.

1013
00:37:06,930 --> 00:37:07,920
-Take it.
-Enough.

1014
00:37:07,920 --> 00:37:08,510
Enough.

1015
00:37:08,550 --> 00:37:09,360
I'm telling you,
if you give it back to me again,

1016
00:37:09,360 --> 00:37:10,230
I'll slap you.

1017
00:37:10,630 --> 00:37:12,000
Mr. Ding, I'm just showing respect

1018
00:37:12,000 --> 00:37:12,930
and you want to slap me?

1019
00:37:12,930 --> 00:37:14,660
It's fine. After you slap me,
I'll still give it to you.

1020
00:37:14,660 --> 00:37:15,310
Get lost.

1021
00:37:16,930 --> 00:37:18,730
Look at you. Talking is useless.

1022
00:37:19,250 --> 00:37:20,910
You're being stubborn again.

1023
00:37:22,990 --> 00:37:24,590
Xiaoman!

1024
00:37:26,630 --> 00:37:27,830
Good news! Good news!

1025
00:37:28,070 --> 00:37:29,880
What good news? Did you find money?

1026
00:37:29,880 --> 00:37:30,480
Close enough.

1027
00:37:30,480 --> 00:37:31,540
You're half right.

1028
00:37:31,710 --> 00:37:33,320
You know that show I filmed in Beijing?

1029
00:37:33,320 --> 00:37:34,450
They hadn't paid me,

1030
00:37:35,480 --> 00:37:36,360
but they finally did.

1031
00:37:36,360 --> 00:37:37,620
You got the money back?

1032
00:37:37,920 --> 00:37:38,650
Impressive.

1033
00:37:39,110 --> 00:37:41,070
We can upgrade now.

1034
00:37:41,810 --> 00:37:44,400
I picked a prime spot
on the commercial street today.

1035
00:37:44,400 --> 00:37:45,890
Business is booming next door.

1036
00:37:45,890 --> 00:37:48,410
I told you we should have moved long ago.

1037
00:37:48,440 --> 00:37:49,840
You finally did something right.

1038
00:37:49,840 --> 00:37:51,180
When have I ever lied to you?

1039
00:37:51,180 --> 00:37:52,710
Right? I never tricked you.

1040
00:37:53,120 --> 00:37:54,520
You fooled me every time.

1041
00:37:56,250 --> 00:37:57,760
When have I ever fooled you?

1042
00:37:57,760 --> 00:37:58,320
Hurry up.

1043
00:37:59,150 --> 00:37:59,840
Slow down.

1044
00:38:00,840 --> 00:38:01,510
Stop.

1045
00:38:01,510 --> 00:38:02,670
What are you doing?

1046
00:38:02,670 --> 00:38:03,190
Yes.

1047
00:38:03,440 --> 00:38:04,100
We're here.

1048
00:38:04,900 --> 00:38:06,480
It's just around the corner.

1049
00:38:06,480 --> 00:38:08,130
Then why don't you ride over there?

1050
00:38:08,130 --> 00:38:09,450
Why ride over there?

1051
00:38:09,710 --> 00:38:11,440
If they see you on such a big bike,

1052
00:38:11,440 --> 00:38:12,670
won't they jack up the price?

1053
00:38:12,670 --> 00:38:14,440
Even riding this thing
would make them jack up the price?

1054
00:38:14,440 --> 00:38:16,370
What do you know? Just listen to me.

1055
00:38:16,400 --> 00:38:16,950
Let's go.

1056
00:38:19,620 --> 00:38:21,710
Do you wear a helmet for a walk?

1057
00:38:23,000 --> 00:38:23,510
I...

1058
00:38:24,070 --> 00:38:25,390
No wonder my throat is scratchy.

1059
00:38:25,390 --> 00:38:26,590
Where should I put it?

1060
00:38:31,220 --> 00:38:32,060
It won't get stolen?

1061
00:38:32,060 --> 00:38:33,460
Who would take that junk?

1062
00:38:34,780 --> 00:38:35,640
Which one is it?

1063
00:38:35,830 --> 00:38:36,630
Just this one.

1064
00:38:37,760 --> 00:38:38,630
This one?

1065
00:38:39,280 --> 00:38:40,550
This place will take forever to clean up.

1066
00:38:40,550 --> 00:38:41,670
We can clean it up.

1067
00:38:44,570 --> 00:38:45,340
Mr. Zhuang.

1068
00:38:45,630 --> 00:38:46,110
Hello.

1069
00:38:46,190 --> 00:38:46,940
Hello.

1070
00:38:47,860 --> 00:38:49,570
This is my partner, Mr. Zhang.

1071
00:38:50,060 --> 00:38:50,560
Hello, Mr. Zhang.

1072
00:38:50,560 --> 00:38:51,640
Great.

1073
00:38:53,000 --> 00:38:54,960
How much is the rent for this shop?

1074
00:38:56,070 --> 00:38:57,930
The landlord wants 15,000 a year.

1075
00:38:58,150 --> 00:38:59,000
15,000?

1076
00:38:59,340 --> 00:39:00,140
That's right.

1077
00:39:00,630 --> 00:39:01,630
This is Tiecheng's

1078
00:39:01,630 --> 00:39:04,630
prime location
on the busiest commercial street.

1079
00:39:04,840 --> 00:39:05,970
That's a fair price.

1080
00:39:06,360 --> 00:39:08,470
It'd be cheaper over on Sidao Street,

1081
00:39:08,770 --> 00:39:11,830
but the foot traffic there
is nothing compared to here.

1082
00:39:12,670 --> 00:39:13,920
15,000 it is then.

1083
00:39:14,190 --> 00:39:14,960
Look.

1084
00:39:16,150 --> 00:39:16,680
Well...

1085
00:39:17,510 --> 00:39:18,440
Wait a second.

1086
00:39:19,330 --> 00:39:20,400
Think about it again. Come here.

1087
00:39:20,400 --> 00:39:21,270
Just think about it.

1088
00:39:21,270 --> 00:39:21,720
No.

1089
00:39:22,450 --> 00:39:23,170
Hold on.

1090
00:39:23,670 --> 00:39:25,110
15,000 for what?

1091
00:39:25,110 --> 00:39:26,710
This... This shop is 15,000?

1092
00:39:27,270 --> 00:39:28,470
And you believe that?

1093
00:39:28,480 --> 00:39:29,550
Listen to me.

1094
00:39:30,840 --> 00:39:32,440
While we were just chatting,

1095
00:39:32,670 --> 00:39:34,070
30 or 40 people walked by.

1096
00:39:34,320 --> 00:39:35,000
You know?

1097
00:39:36,830 --> 00:39:38,140
In every aspect,

1098
00:39:38,530 --> 00:39:39,930
this is a prime location.

1099
00:39:40,400 --> 00:39:42,660
This shop is about 40 or 50 square meters.

1100
00:39:44,290 --> 00:39:45,690
Wait, think about it.

1101
00:39:45,950 --> 00:39:47,490
He used to sell tofu pudding.

1102
00:39:47,490 --> 00:39:48,280
15,000 a year?

1103
00:39:48,280 --> 00:39:49,320
Could we earn that back?

1104
00:39:49,320 --> 00:39:51,680
Plus, this place is a mess.
It'll cost money to fix.

1105
00:39:51,680 --> 00:39:52,540
Do you trust me?

1106
00:39:53,070 --> 00:39:54,270
15,000 is a good deal.

1107
00:39:54,510 --> 00:39:55,550
When do we sign?

1108
00:39:56,030 --> 00:39:58,070
How about this? Today,

1109
00:39:58,070 --> 00:39:59,230
pay a 10,000 deposit first.

1110
00:39:59,230 --> 00:40:01,090
We'll sign the contract in a week.

1111
00:40:01,440 --> 00:40:01,960
What?

1112
00:40:03,510 --> 00:40:04,960
Pay before signing the contract?

1113
00:40:04,960 --> 00:40:05,760
That won't do.

1114
00:40:05,780 --> 00:40:07,700
No, listen to me.

1115
00:40:07,730 --> 00:40:08,790
Look at this house.

1116
00:40:08,810 --> 00:40:10,440
Before handing the place over to you,

1117
00:40:10,440 --> 00:40:11,940
shouldn't the landlord clean it up first?

1118
00:40:11,940 --> 00:40:14,360
Just imagine—
if you sign the contract today,

1119
00:40:14,360 --> 00:40:15,480
the time spent fixing up the place

1120
00:40:15,480 --> 00:40:17,070
will count as part of your lease.

1121
00:40:17,070 --> 00:40:18,330
You'd be taking a loss.

1122
00:40:20,360 --> 00:40:21,030
Okay.

1123
00:40:22,550 --> 00:40:23,750
Then go get the money.

1124
00:40:23,960 --> 00:40:24,480
Get the money.

1125
00:40:24,480 --> 00:40:25,140
What money?

1126
00:40:25,150 --> 00:40:26,710
Is there a receipt for that money?

1127
00:40:26,710 --> 00:40:28,590
Yes, I have it all ready.

1128
00:40:28,870 --> 00:40:29,870
Wait a bit longer.

1129
00:40:30,760 --> 00:40:31,360
Wait a bit.

1130
00:40:31,360 --> 00:40:32,110
I'm withdrawing money.

1131
00:40:32,110 --> 00:40:32,800
I'll give it to you when I get back.

1132
00:40:32,800 --> 00:40:33,550
Withdrawing...

1133
00:40:33,550 --> 00:40:35,230
You didn't bring any money?

1134
00:40:35,390 --> 00:40:36,140
Just wait.

1135
00:40:36,880 --> 00:40:38,080
This place is really expensive.

1136
00:40:38,080 --> 00:40:39,440
Yeah, it costs over 10,000.

1137
00:40:39,440 --> 00:40:41,000
Then I'll wait.

1138
00:40:41,930 --> 00:40:42,990
There's one thing.

1139
00:40:46,060 --> 00:40:47,910
You know this crew—those guys.

1140
00:40:48,760 --> 00:40:49,960
They should just transfer the money.

1141
00:40:49,960 --> 00:40:51,360
Why pay in installments?

1142
00:40:51,840 --> 00:40:52,800
I'm short on cash.

1143
00:40:52,800 --> 00:40:53,630
How much are you short?

1144
00:40:53,630 --> 00:40:54,360
Over 2,000.

1145
00:40:56,070 --> 00:40:57,200
I have it. I'll pay.

1146
00:41:00,510 --> 00:41:01,170
You have it?

1147
00:41:01,290 --> 00:41:03,280
I'll go withdraw it.
I don't have it on me.

1148
00:41:03,280 --> 00:41:03,880
Withdraw?

1149
00:41:05,000 --> 00:41:06,260
This is embarrassing.

1150
00:41:06,670 --> 00:41:07,630
I borrow from you every time,

1151
00:41:07,630 --> 00:41:08,710
but never pay you back.

1152
00:41:08,710 --> 00:41:09,550
Call it an investment.

1153
00:41:09,550 --> 00:41:10,400
Still investing?

1154
00:41:10,400 --> 00:41:10,840
Yes.

1155
00:41:11,760 --> 00:41:13,480
How many shares do I have now?

1156
00:41:13,690 --> 00:41:14,330
50.

1157
00:41:15,520 --> 00:41:16,560
Okay. Let's go.

1158
00:41:17,070 --> 00:41:17,590
Sure.

1159
00:41:17,590 --> 00:41:18,150
Okay.

1160
00:41:18,430 --> 00:41:19,280
Why not?

1161
00:41:19,280 --> 00:41:20,440
50 shares

1162
00:41:20,460 --> 00:41:21,190
is plenty.

1163
00:41:23,230 --> 00:41:24,290
You're something.

1164
00:41:27,030 --> 00:41:28,360
Mom, Dad, Xia Lei is here.

1165
00:41:28,360 --> 00:41:29,160
Hello, Uncle.

1166
00:41:30,780 --> 00:41:31,880
-Xia Lei, you're here.
-Hello, Aunt.

1167
00:41:31,880 --> 00:41:33,550
You haven't visited in a while.

1168
00:41:33,550 --> 00:41:34,770
School keeps you busy?

1169
00:41:34,770 --> 00:41:35,450
It's okay.

1170
00:41:35,690 --> 00:41:38,890
These are some local specialties
from my parents for you.

1171
00:41:39,110 --> 00:41:40,400
Your parents gave them to you.

1172
00:41:40,400 --> 00:41:42,150
You should keep them for yourself.

1173
00:41:42,150 --> 00:41:43,840
I set these aside for you.

1174
00:41:43,860 --> 00:41:45,000
Mine are still in the dorm.

1175
00:41:45,000 --> 00:41:45,800
I have plenty.

1176
00:41:45,830 --> 00:41:46,500
Okay.

1177
00:41:47,080 --> 00:41:49,040
He can't cook at school,

1178
00:41:49,070 --> 00:41:50,280
especially things like mushrooms.

1179
00:41:50,280 --> 00:41:51,320
I'll take these inside.

1180
00:41:51,320 --> 00:41:51,700
Okay.

1181
00:41:51,720 --> 00:41:52,720
I'll cook for you.

1182
00:41:53,430 --> 00:41:54,720
Sit down.

1183
00:41:58,230 --> 00:41:59,760
How have you been recently?

1184
00:42:01,000 --> 00:42:02,920
My schoolwork is fine.

1185
00:42:03,360 --> 00:42:05,000
The schedule isn't too packed.

1186
00:42:05,000 --> 00:42:06,000
I was thinking,

1187
00:42:06,760 --> 00:42:08,110
since I have so much time,

1188
00:42:08,110 --> 00:42:09,590
why not do an internship

1189
00:42:10,630 --> 00:42:12,280
to gain some experience?

1190
00:42:13,070 --> 00:42:14,930
Have you found an internship yet?

1191
00:42:15,950 --> 00:42:17,360
I'm still looking.

1192
00:42:17,380 --> 00:42:19,010
I've sent out some resumes,

1193
00:42:19,040 --> 00:42:21,330
but haven't heard back yet.

1194
00:42:21,760 --> 00:42:22,490
Don't worry.

1195
00:42:23,400 --> 00:42:24,480
I have a friend

1196
00:42:24,480 --> 00:42:26,630
who runs a decent company
here in Shanghai.

1197
00:42:26,630 --> 00:42:27,920
Why don't I talk to him

1198
00:42:27,920 --> 00:42:29,230
and get you an internship there?

1199
00:42:29,230 --> 00:42:31,670
The major might not be a perfect match,

1200
00:42:31,840 --> 00:42:33,440
but gaining some work experience

1201
00:42:33,440 --> 00:42:34,590
will definitely be good.

1202
00:42:34,590 --> 00:42:35,510
Then I'll...

1203
00:42:35,510 --> 00:42:36,800
let me thank you in advance, Uncle Yan.

1204
00:42:36,800 --> 00:42:37,480
Don't thank me yet.

1205
00:42:37,480 --> 00:42:38,810
Wait until I get it done.

1206
00:42:39,190 --> 00:42:40,070
His company

1207
00:42:40,070 --> 00:42:41,320
is quite large,

1208
00:42:41,950 --> 00:42:44,150
and has good prospects.

1209
00:42:44,180 --> 00:42:44,960
Just do it for now.

1210
00:42:44,960 --> 00:42:46,320
You have to work hard, right?

1211
00:42:46,320 --> 00:42:47,710
Sure. If I can get in,

1212
00:42:47,710 --> 00:42:49,570
I'll definitely work extra hard.

1213
00:42:50,280 --> 00:42:51,990
Are you dropping the website?

1214
00:42:52,920 --> 00:42:54,840
I just feel that website

1215
00:42:55,800 --> 00:42:57,030
isn't very reliable.

1216
00:42:57,150 --> 00:42:59,760
I think I should intern first

1217
00:42:59,780 --> 00:43:01,180
to gain some experience.

1218
00:43:01,220 --> 00:43:01,990
Yes.

1219
00:43:02,030 --> 00:43:03,800
Work experience is very important.
